title: Appointments to Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
The Government announced today (November 30) the re-appointment of five members 
and appointment of one member to the Hospital Authority (HA) for a two-year term 
with effect from December 1, 2006.  Ms Vivien Chan, Professor Fok Tai-fai, Mr Edward Ho Sing-tin, Dr the Hon Joseph 
Lee Kok-long and Mr John Lee Luen-wai have been re-appointed as members to the 
HA. Dr Donald Li Kwok-tung has been appointed as a new member. Dr Li is a

private medical practitioner and a member of the Hospital Governing Committee of 
Our Lady of Maryknoll Hospital. The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, thanked outgoing 
members Dr the Hon Kwok Ka-ki for his advice and contribution to the HA. He will 
retire from the HA Board with effect from December 1, 2006. The Hospital Authority, as from December 1, 2006, will comprise a chairman, 19 
non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the
